block content
    // Header
    header.masthead
      .container
        .intro-text
          .intro-lead-in Welcome To Our School!
          .intro-heading.text-uppercase It's Nice To Meet You
          a.btn.btn-primary.btn-xl.text-uppercase.js-scroll-trigger(href='#languages') Learn More
    // Languages
    section#languages
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12.text-center
            h2.section-heading.text-uppercase Languages
            h3.section-subheading.text-muted All languages are teached in 3 different types of courses.
        .row.text-center
          .col-md-4
            span(width='120', height='120')
              img.img-fluid.img-circle.center-block(src='/images/languages/united_kingdom_round_icon_256.png', alt='UK_flag', width='auto')
              // i.fa.fa-circle.fa-stack-2x.text-primary
              // i.fa.fa-shopping-cart.fa-stack-1x.fa-inverse
            h4.languages-heading English
            p.text-muted
              | English is the third most widespread native language in the world, after Standard Chinese and Spanish. It is the most widely learned second language and is either the official language or one of the official languages in almost 60 sovereign states.
          .col-md-4
            span(width='120', height='120')
              img.img-fluid.img-circle.center-block(src='/images/languages/germany_round_icon_256.png', alt='UK_flag', width='auto')
              // i.fa.fa-circle.fa-stack-2x.text-primary
              // i.fa.fa-laptop.fa-stack-1x.fa-inverse
            h4.languages-heading German
            p.text-muted
              | One of the major languages of the world, German is the first language of about 95 million people worldwide and the most widely spoken native language in the European Union. German also is the fourth most widely taught non-English language in the US and third in the EU.
          .col-md-4
            span(width='120', height='120')
              img.img-fluid.img-circle.center-block(src='/images/languages/spain_round_icon_256.png', alt='UK_flag', width='auto')
              // i.fa.fa-circle.fa-stack-2x.text-primary
              // i.fa.fa-lock.fa-stack-1x.fa-inverse
            h4.languages-heading Spanish
            p.text-muted
              | Spanish is the official or national language in Spain, Equatorial Guinea, and 19 countries in the Americas. Speakers in the Americas total some 418 million. In the EU, Spanish is the mother tongue of 8% of the population. Spanish is the most popular second language learned in the US.
    // Courses Grid
    section#courses.bg-light
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12.text-center
